== Events == * {{ill|Anwa|ja|安和|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[969]] {{ill|April 14|ja|4月14日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – In the incident known as {{ill|Anwa no Hen|ja|安和の変|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, due to a denunciation by Genmanaka, 【Minamoto Takamasa】 (源高明) conspired to depose Crown Prince Morihei (守平親王) and was demoted to the Rank of 【Dazaiken-sui|大宰権帥】; this marked the establishment of the Fujiwara regency. * {{ill|Tenroku|ja|天禄|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[970]] {{ill|May 3|ja|5月3日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The era name was changed from {{ill|Anwa|ja|安和|12=draft|12=draft}} to {{ill|Tenroku|ja|天禄|12=draft|12=draft}}. * ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1356]] {{ill|April 26|ja|4月26日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Nijō Yoshimoto compiled Japan’s first renga anthology, the {{ill|Utsubunashū|ja|菟玖波集|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|12=draft|12=draft}} 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1826]] {{ill|May 1|ja|5月1日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Philip Franz von Siebold|ja|シーボルト|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, while accompanying the head of the Dutch trading post, attempted to export Japanese maps and other prohibited items, and was subsequently expelled. * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1870]] {{ill|April 25|ja|4月25日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Surveying for Japan’s first railway between Tokyo and Kanagawa began.
== Births == * {{ill|Kashō|ja|嘉祥|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[850]] {{ill|May 10|ja|5月10日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Emperor Seiwa|ja|正和天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 56th Emperor of Japan (died [[880]]). * [[Keichō]] 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1604]] {{ill|April 24|ja|4月24日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Matsudaira Naomoto|ja|松平直基|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, lord of the Echizen, Ōno, Yamagata, and Himeji Domains (died [[1648]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft}} 15th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1844]] {{ill|May 12|ja|5月12日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Unii Ryūo|ja|雲井龍雄|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military official and politician from the Yonezawa Domain (died [[1870]]). * 明治2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1869]] {{ill|May 6|ja|5月6日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Inoue Junosuke|ja|井上準之助|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a politician (died [[1932]]). * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1872]] {{ill|May 2|ja|5月2日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Higuchi Ichiyō|ja|樋口一葉|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a novelist and waka poet (died [[1896]]).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Taika|ja|大化|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[649]] {{ill|May 11|ja|5月11日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Soga Kurayamada Ishikawa Maro|ja|蘇我倉山田石川麻呂|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a noble and grandson of {{ill|Soga Umako|ja|蘇我馬子|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Meio|ja|明応|12=draft|12=draft}} 8th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1499]] {{ill|May 5|ja|5月5日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Rennyo|ja|蓮如|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the founder of Jōdo Shinshū (born [[1415]]).
