|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1870]] {{ill|April 25|ja|4月25日}}) – Surveying for Japan’s first railway between Tokyo and Kanagawa began.
== Births == * {{ill|Kashō|ja|嘉祥}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} [[850]] {{ill|May 10|ja|5月10日}}) – {{ill|Emperor Seiwa|ja|正和天皇}}, the 56th Emperor of Japan (died [[880]]). * [[Keichō]] 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1604]] {{ill|April 24|ja|4月24日}}) – {{ill|Matsudaira Naomoto|ja|松平直基}}, lord of the Echizen, Ōno, Yamagata, and Himeji Domains (died [[1648]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保}} 15th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1844]] {{ill|May 12|ja|5月12日}}) – {{ill|Unii Ryūo|ja|雲井龍雄}}, a military official and politician from the Yonezawa Domain (died [[1870]]). * 明治2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1869]] {{ill|May 6|ja|5月6日}}) – {{ill|Inoue Junosuke|ja|井上準之助}}, a politician (died [[1932]]). * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1872]] {{ill|May 2|ja|5月2日}}) – {{ill|Higuchi Ichiyō|ja|樋口一葉}}, a novelist and waka poet (died [[1896]]).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Taika|ja|大化}} 5th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} [[649]] {{ill|May 11|ja|5月11日}}) – {{ill|Soga Kurayamada Ishikawa Maro|ja|蘇我倉山田石川麻呂}}, a noble and grandson of {{ill|Soga Umako|ja|蘇我馬子}}. * {{ill|Meio|ja|明応}} 8th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} [[1499]] {{ill|May 5|ja|5月5日}}) – {{ill|Rennyo|ja|蓮如}}, the founder of Jōdo Shinshū (born [[1415]]).
