companying the head of the Dutch trading post, attempted to export Japanese maps and other prohibited items, and was subsequently expelled. * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}} [[1870]] {{ill|April 25|ja|4月25日|qq=|12=draft}}) – Surveying for Japan’s first railway between Tokyo and Kanagawa began.
