{{Not to be confused with|March 25|qq=March 25}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=三月廿五|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 3월 25일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 25''' is the 25th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senbu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Anna (era)|Anwa]] 2nd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[969]] [[:en:April 14|April 14]]) – In the incident known as {{ill|Anwa no Hen|ja|安和の変|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Anwa no Hen|qq=}}, due to a denunciation by Genmanaka, 【Minamoto Takamasa】 (源高明) conspired to depose Crown Prince Morihei (守平親王) and was demoted to the Rank of 【Dazaiken-sui|大宰権帥】; this marked the establishment of the Fujiwara regency. * [[:en:Tenroku|Tenroku]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[970]] [[:en:May 3|May 3]]) – The era name was changed from [[:en:Anna (era)|Anwa]] to [[:en:Tenroku|Tenroku]]. * ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1356|1356]] [[:en:April 26|April 26]]) – Nijō Yoshimoto compiled Japan’s first renga anthology, the [[:en:Tsukubashū|Utsubunashū]]. * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 9th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1826|1826]] [[:en:May 1|May 1]]) – {{ill|Philip Franz von Siebold|ja|シーボルト|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Philip Franz von Siebold|qq=}}, while accompanying the head of the Dutch trading post, attempted to export Japanese maps and other prohibited items, and was subsequently expelled. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1870]] [[:en:April 25|April 25]]) – Surveying for Japan’s first railway between Tokyo and Kanagawa began.
== Births == * [[:en:Kashō|Kashō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[850]] [[:en:May 10|May 10]]) – {{ill|Emperor Seiwa|ja|正和天皇|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Seiwa|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, the 56th Emperor of Japan (died [[880]]). * [[Keichō]] 9th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1604|1604]] [[:en:April 24|April 24]]) – {{ill|Matsudaira Naomoto|ja|松平直基|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsudaira Naomoto|qq=}}, lord of the Echizen, Ōno, Yamagata, and Himeji Domains (died [[:en:1648|1648]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 15th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1844|1844]] [[:en:May 12|May 12]]) – {{ill|Unii Ryūo|ja|雲井龍雄|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Unii Ryūo|qq=}}, a military official and politician from the Yonezawa Domain (died [[1870]]). * 明治2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1869]] [[:en:May 6|May 6]]) – [[:en:Junnosuke Inoue|Inoue Junosuke]], a politician (died [[1932]]). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1872]] [[:en:May 2|May 2]]) – [[:en:Ichiyō Higuchi|Higuchi Ichiyō]], a novelist and waka poet (died [[1896]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Taika (era)|Taika]] 5th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[649]] [[:en:May 11|May 11]]) – [[:en:Soga no Kurayamada no Ishikawa no Maro|Soga Kurayamada Ishikawa Maro]], a noble and grandson of [[:en:Soga no Umako|Soga Umako]]. * [[:en:Meiō|Meio]] 8th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1499|1499]] [[:en:May 5|May 5]]) – [[:en:Rennyo|Rennyo]], the founder of Jōdo Shinshū (born [[:en:1415|1415]]).
