== Births == * [[:en:Kashō|Kashō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:850|850]] [[:en:May 10|May 10]]) – {{ill|Emperor Seiwa|ja|正和天皇|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Seiwa|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, the 56th Emperor of Japan (died [[:en:880|880]]). * [[Keichō]] 9th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1604|1604]] [[:en:April 24|April 24]]) – {{ill|Matsudaira Naomoto|ja|松平直基|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsudaira Naomoto|qq=}}, lord of the Echizen, Ōno, Yamagata, and Himeji Domains (died [[:en:1648|1648]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 15th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1844|1844]] [[:en:May 12|May 12]]) – {{ill|Unii Ryūo|ja|雲井龍雄|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Unii Ryūo|qq=}}, a military official and politician from the Yonezawa Domain (died [[:en:1870|1870]]). * 明治2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1869|1869]] [[:en:May 6|May 6]]) – [[:en:Junnosuke Inoue|Inoue Junosuke]], a politician (died [[:en:1932|1932]]). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1872|1872]] [[:en:May 2|May 2]]) – [[:en:Ichiyō Higuchi|Higuchi Ichiyō]], a novelist and waka poet (died [[:en:1896|1896]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Taika (era)|Taika]] 5th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:649|649]] [[:en:May 11|May 11]]) – [[:en:Soga no Kurayamada no Ishikawa no Maro|Soga Kurayamada Ishikawa Maro]], a noble and grandson of [[:en:Soga no Umako|Soga Umako]]. * [[:en:Meiō|Meio]] 8th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1499|1499]] [[:en:May 5|May 5]]) – [[:en:Rennyo|Rennyo]], the founder of Jōdo Shinshū (born [[:en:1415|1415]]).
